OL,3,CCould there be a coalition in Coventry?
OL,5,FAfter Coventry's City Council election
OL,6,Fresults, no party has overall control,
OL,7,Fmeaning coalition talks are highly
OL,8,Flikely.
OL,10,FThe people of Coventry have voted for
OL,11,Fchange in the local elections
OL,12,Fyesterday, with the make up of the
OL,13,Fcity council completely changed.
OL,15,FWhilst Labour are still the biggest
OL,16,Fparty, they no longer have the
OL,17,Fmajority. The Conservatives are now
OL,18,Fthe third party, instead of the
OL,19,Fsecond. Reform UK made huge gains.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/4
